      "The practice Murphy identifies as most critical across all four shifts is what he calls the \"architect of impact\" function: the ability to connect business outcomes to product decisions clearly enough that anyone in the organisation can see the through-line. It requires business acumen, strategic thinking, and the ability to influence without authority — none of which AI compresses. The PMs who thrive in this environment are the ones who treat AI as a tool that frees time, not one that changes what that time should be used for. The ones struggling are the ones who used that free time to do more of what they were already doing.",
